00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Curved smartphones, curved screens and fingerprint scanners. Smartphone makers are trying to apply new features to their top tier smartphones. Some are successful and some aren't.

00:00:28.210 --> 00:00:38.700
You are watching the Unboxholics show and this is the Samsung Galaxy Note Edge.

00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:41.900
Before taking a closer look at the phone, let's see what's inside the retail box.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:52.800
The Galaxy Note Edge arrived in a quite premium package. Aside from the usual manuals and accessories, there is a leather case that can be folded.

00:00:52.900 --> 00:01:01.200
Although the Note Edge is a high end device, Samsung decided to include average and common earphones.

00:01:01.415 --> 00:01:10.500
As soon as I removed the protective cover, the "Edge Screen" attracted my attention immediately.

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:33.090
Regarding the overall build quality, Samsung tried really hard to deliver a high quality device that is pleasing to the eyes and hands of the user. 

00:01:33.155 --> 00:01:48.400
Aside from the main speaker, the back side also features a fingerprint scanner which I still do not find useful in smartphones. 

00:01:48.546 --> 00:01:55.500
The S-Pen is a common characteristic of the Note smartphone series and it could not be missing from the Galaxy Note Edge. 

00:01:55.553 --> 00:02:00.000
Let's take a look at the dimensions of the Note Edge...

